HEADWORD: Stalagmite
<hw>Sta*lag"mite</hw> <pr>(st⟦adot⟧*l⟦acr⟧g"m⟦imac⟧t)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>sta`lagma</grk> that which drops, a drop,
fr. <grk>stala`zein</grk> to drop: cf. F. <ets>stalagmite</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A deposit more or less resembling an inverted
stalactite, formed by calcareous water dropping on the floors of
caverns; hence, a similar deposit of other material.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stalagmitical</ent>⟦br⟧
